This paper deals with the study of directability of fuzzy and nondeterministic automata, which falls under the category of formal languages and automata theory. Therefore, cs.FL (Formal Languages and Automata Theory) is the most likely sub-category. The paper also involves the study of closure properties, which is related to logic and set theory, making cs.LO (Logic in Computer Science) another likely sub-category. The paper also involves the study of sets and their properties, which falls under the category of data structures (cs.DS). The paper also involves the study of decision-making and computation, which falls under the category of artificial intelligence (cs.AI). Finally, the paper involves the study of homomorphic images and finite direct products, which falls under the category of programming languages (cs.PL).
